<HEADLINE>
US and North Korea hold further bilateral meeting
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
BEIJING, Aug 1
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States and North Korea Monday 
held another bilateral meeting, their seventh in a week, as they 
continue to work together to find a solution to the nuclear 
standoff, sources said.
</P>
<P>
Their meeting was one of several that took place Monday morning 
between the six nations taking part in negotiations to convince the 
Stalinist state to abandon its atomic weapons programs.
</P>
<P>
"There was a bilateral meeting between South Korea and the US, 
and then China met North Korea and South Korea, and then North Korea 
and the US met," said a source close to the negotiations who did not 
want to be identified.
</P>
<P>
It was not clear how long the meetings lasted.
</P>
<P>
The United States and North Korea have met seven times in the 
past week amid wider international talks on Pyongyang's nuclear 
weapons program.
</P>
